## Phase 4: Add Risk Gatekeeper

**Goal:** Separate signal generation from trade permission. Inspired by `boooot`'s [Gatekeeper](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/tmp/boooot_compare_2/trading_system/trading_system/gatekeeper/gatekeeper.py#20-301).

### [MODIFY] [risk.rs](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/bot/risk.rs)

Add:

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize)]
pub enum GateDecision {
    Approved { reason: String },
    Blocked { reason: FilterReason },
}

pub struct Gatekeeper {
    emergency_halt: bool,
    daily_loss_limit: f64,
    daily_pnl: f64,
    trading_date: Option<chrono::NaiveDate>,
    cooldown_until: Option<u64>,
    // ... existing filter config
}

impl Gatekeeper {
    pub fn check_entry(&mut self, snapshot: &MarketSnapshot, ...) -> GateDecision;
    pub fn record_trade_result(&mut self, pnl: f64);
    pub fn halt(&mut self);
    pub fn clear_halt(&mut self);
}
```

Key features ported from `boooot`:
- Daily loss limit auto-halt (the most valuable feature)
- Emergency kill switch
- Cooldown after loss
- All existing [trade_allowed](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/bot/risk.rs#36-73) checks preserved

---

## Phase 5: Structured Event Logging

**Goal:** Typed event logging for replay determinism and debugging.

### [MODIFY] [logging.rs](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/bot/logging.rs)

Add `EngineEvent` enum (for logging/observability only, **not** a runtime event bus):

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Serialize)]
#[serde(tag = "type")]
pub enum EngineEvent {
    BookUpdate { ts: u64, yes_bid: f64, yes_ask: f64, no_bid: f64, no_ask: f64 },
    StrategySignal { ts: u64, entry: String, exit: String, midpoint: f64 },
    GateDecision { ts: u64, decision: String, reason: String },
    ShadowEntry { ts: u64, side: String, price: f64, size: f64 },
    ShadowExit { ts: u64, pnl: f64, bankroll: f64 },
    EmergencyHalt { ts: u64, daily_pnl: f64 },
}
```

Separate JSONL log files: `market_events.jsonl`, `strategy_events.jsonl`, `execution_events.jsonl`.

---

## Phase 6: Feed Normalization + WebSocket Live Feed

**Goal:** Make [watch_btc_market](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/commands/bot.rs#365-672) event-driven via WebSocket instead of REST polling.

### [MODIFY] [feed.rs](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/bot/feed.rs)

[MarketWebsocketFeed](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/bot/feed.rs#159-163) already exists and works. Changes needed:
- Remove [fetch_snapshot](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/commands/bot.rs#1483-1564) REST polling from [watch_btc_market](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/commands/bot.rs#365-672)
- Consume [BookDeltaEvent](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/bot/feed.rs#43-57) from the WebSocket feed directly
- Add `StrategyInputSource` trait:

```rust
pub trait StrategyInputSource {
    fn next_event(&mut self) -> Option<BookDeltaEvent>;
    fn current_time(&self) -> u64;
}
```

### [MODIFY] [bot.rs](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/commands/bot.rs)

Rewrite [watch_btc_market](file:///c:/Users/mehul/OneDrive/Desktop/Studio/PROJECTS/polycli/polycli/src/commands/bot.rs#365-672) loop to consume `StrategyInputSource` instead of REST polling.

